title: Arlington Heights Urban Panorama
description: A sweeping vista across Arlington's residential neighborhoods reveals the architectural tapestry of Northern Virginia's most iconic skyline. Bare winter trees frame the composition while the Potomac River and distant monuments anchor the expansive view, creating a meditative study of urban density meeting natural landscape.
location: Arlington, Virginia - overlooking Washington DC metropolitan area

title: Monument and Flight Over the Capital
description: A striking composition capturing an aircraft suspended above Washington DC's iconic monuments, with the Washington Monument prominently centered against the city's architectural landscape. The interplay of urban geometry and aerial perspective creates a powerful meditation on human achievement and movement.
location: Washington Monument, National Mall, Washington DC

title: Monument Illuminated in Twilight
description: A towering neoclassical obelisk stands sentinel against a deep indigo sky, its marble surface glowing with ethereal light. This iconic memorial captures the quiet dignity of Washington DC's most recognizable landmark, rendered in contemplative tones that emphasize timeless architectural grace.

title: Lincoln Memorial Reflected in Still Waters
description: A masterwork of symmetry and contemplation, this image captures the iconic Lincoln Memorial in perfect reflection upon the Reflecting Pool. The composition emphasizes the monumental architecture's dignified presence, framed by the disciplined geometry of tree-lined pathways and crystalline water, creating a meditation on permanence and democratic ideals.
location: The National Mall, Washington DC - Lincoln Memorial and Reflecting Pool

title: Potomac Reflections at Night
description: A serene urban waterscape capturing the interplay of architectural illumination and water reflection along Washington DC's iconic waterfront. The composition balances geometric precision with organic movement, creating a contemplative study of light, color, and urban landscape.
location: Potomac River, Washington DC - Georgetown to Kennedy Center area
